				{
					"name": "Token Refresh",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"const response = pm.response.json();\r",
									"pm.environment.set(\"accessToken\", response.access);\r",
									""
								],
								"type": "text/javascript",
								"packages": {}
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n  \"refresh\": \"{{refreshToken}}\"\n}"
						},
						"url": "{{base_url}}/api/users/token/refresh/",
						"description": "## POST Token Refresh\n\nThis endpoint is used to refresh the user authentication token. It requires a valid refresh token to issue a new access token.\n\n### Request\n\n- **URL:** `{{base_url}}/api/users/token/refresh/`\n    \n- **Method:** POST\n    \n- **Content-Type:** application/json\n    \n\n#### Request Body\n\nThe request body must be in JSON format and include the following parameter:\n\n- **refresh** (string): The refresh token used to obtain a new access token. This should be replaced with the `refreshToken` from the environment variables.\n    \n\n**Example:**\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"refresh\": \"{{refreshToken}}\"\n}\n\n ```\n\n### Response\n\n- **Status Code:** 401 Unauthorized\n    \n- **Content-Type:** application/json\n    \n- {\"detail\": \"\",\"code\": \"\"}\n    \n\nA 401 status indicates that the provided refresh token is invalid or expired. Ensure that the refresh token is valid before making this request."
					},
					"response": []
				},
